sql:
SELECT listing_id, neighborhood
FROM listings
WHERE rent_sqft_cat = 2;

external_knowledge:
- "a handful of properties" metaphorically means more than 2 properties;
- "rent is not too steep" refers to an average rent less than 3000;
- "offer the best bargain" indicates sorting by average rent in ascending order.

- "shining stars in the housing market" refers to regions with high average rents;
- "outshining the golden city of Los Angeles" implies regions with average rents higher than that of Los Angeles;
- "setting their own luminous standard" denotes a minimum average rent above $3000.

- 'big city of Los Angeles' refers to the region 'losangeles';
- 'typical monthly costs' refer to the average monthly rent;
- 'living spaces' refer to the average square footage of properties;
- 'bathroom counts' refer to the average number of bathrooms in the region.
